OL,3,CWorker sacked for saying 'top of the
OL,4,Cmorning to ya' wins unfair dismissal
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FAn engineering storeman sacked after
OL,8,Fsaying to a colleague "top the morning
OL,9,Fto ya" in a mock Irish accent has won
OL,10,Fmore than #16,000 for unfair dismissal.
OL,12,FKarl Davies, then 57, was working at
OL,13,FWrexham's Oscar Mayer ready meal
OL,14,Fmanufacturing site when, on August 13
OL,15,F2024, he greeted a manager, Scott
OL,16,FMillward, in the accent while
OL,17,Flistening to Irish music, an
OL,18,Femployment tribunal heard.
