OL,3,CWorker sacked for saying 'top of the
OL,4,Cmorning to ya' wins unfair dismissal
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FThe judge said that Mr Davies adopted
OL,8,Fan accent in a "reprehensible" and
OL,9,F"mocking" way and goaded Mr Millward
OL,10,Fby repeating the phrase "in a manner
OL,11,Fthat Mr Millward was bound to find
OL,12,Firritating and embarrassing".
OL,14,FHe said that the claimant was trying
OL,15,Fto get on Mr Millward's nerves to get
OL,16,Fa reaction from him and to cause him
OL,17,Fembarrassment.
OL,26,@pD@POUpD@^O]qD@AOUqD@IO]rD@YOUtD@\O]
