OL,3,CWorker sacked for saying 'top of the
OL,4,Cmorning to ya' wins unfair dismissal
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FHe added: "I find that the purpose was
OL,8,Fnot to racially harass Mr Millward,
OL,9,Fand there is no evidence before me
OL,10,Fthat it had the effect, either, on
OL,11,Fanyone.
OL,13,F"It was nevertheless blameworthy as
OL,14,F(Mr Davies) was subordinate to Mr
OL,15,FMillward.
OL,17,F"It gave rise to the disciplinary
OL,18,Fproceedings and therefore contributed
OL,19,Fto the eventual sanction."
