OL,3,CWorker sacked for saying 'top of the
OL,4,Cmorning to ya' wins unfair dismissal
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FThe claimant did not know and had not
OL,8,Fseen the auditor, who is not known or
OL,9,Fbelieved to be Irish, the tribunal
OL,10,Fheard.
OL,12,FA manager, against whom Mr Davies had
OL,13,Fan unresolved grievance, conducted the
OL,14,Finvestigation into Mr Millward's
OL,15,Fcomments, the tribunal was told.
OL,17,FThe judge wrote that Oscar Mayer's
OL,18,Fdisciplinary case was based on its
OL,19,Fperception that Mr Davies may have
OL,20,Fperceived that the auditor looked
OL,21,F"typically Irish".
OL,26,@}D@AOU}D@QO]
