OL,3,CWorker sacked for saying 'top of the
OL,4,Cmorning to ya' wins unfair dismissal
OL,5,Cclaim
OL,7,FThe judge said: "The claimant was
OL,8,Faccused of using an employment ending,
OL,9,Freputation damaging, loss-inducing,
OL,10,Fracially motivated slur, a slur which
OL,11,Fcould have created an intimidating,
OL,12,Fhostile, degrading, humiliating or
OL,13,Foffensive working environment; these
OL,14,Fare serious matters.
OL,16,F"On the facts peculiar to this case, I
OL,17,Ffound that the dismissal was unfair,
OL,18,Fwhich does not mean that I approve the
OL,19,Fuse of the greeting in question or the
OL,20,Fuse of mock accents."
